<subsection xml:id="subsec-displacement-time-graph">
    <title>Displacement Time Graph of Different Situations</title>
    <activity xml:id="auto_ado8sxfm">
        <p xml:id="auto_k3q8zqkb">
            <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_n89zn2nx">
            A motorist travels from Limuru to Kisumu. The table below shows the distances covered at different times:
        </p>
        <tabular halign="left" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium" bottom="medium">
            <row>
                <cell>Time</cell>
                <cell><m>\text{Distance (km)}</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>\text{9:00 AM}</m></cell>
                <cell><m>0</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>\text{10:00 AM}</m></cell>
                <cell><m>80</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>\text{11:00 AM}</m></cell>
                <cell><m>160</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>\text{11:30 AM}</m></cell>
                <cell><m>160</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
                <cell><m>\text{12:00 PM}</m></cell>
                <cell><m>210</m></cell>
            </row>
        </tabular>
        <p xml:id="auto_fqou61xr">
            Plot the graph using the data given in the table and use it to answer the questions below
            <ol xml:id="auto_6qbh810x" marker="a).">
                <li xml:id="auto_7jl2mqns">
                    <p xml:id="auto_27fz9blx">
                        How far was the motorist from Limuru at 10:30 AM?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_2riafadg">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ivsa7i4d">
                        What was the average speed during the first part of the journey?
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_h3s66ii1">
                    <p xml:id="auto_y6nngxrr">
                        What was the overall average speed?
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
    <insight xml:id="auto_wp51i75u">
        <p xml:id="auto_hs3yd2vc">
          <term>Distance</term> is the total length of the path traveled by an object. 
       </p>
       <p xml:id="auto_mfceuhes">
            <term>Displacement</term> is the shortest distance from the initial to the final position of an object, represented as a vector.
        </p>

        <p xml:id="auto_b95l7stk">
         When distance is plotted against time, a distance-time graph is obtained.
        </p>
    </insight>
    
    
    <example xml:id="auto_fhxwy6hd">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_2t7di0in">
                A car moves with a constant velocity of <m>\text{5 m/s}</m> for <m>8</m> seconds. 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_4d1s4yr2">
                Draw the displacement-time graph and determine the displacement at <m>\text{t = 6s}</m>.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_vvoo7wjm">
                Since the velocity is constant, the displacement increases linearly with time
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_ywfry5bo">
                Hence , <md>
                    <mrow> \text{s = vt} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_9fpkgkj8">
                at <m>\text{t = 6s}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_sjbh98nv">
                <md>
                    <mrow> \text{S = 5} \, \times \, \text{6 = 30} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_pcq2plxw">
                
            </p>
            <image width="60%">
                <latex-image label="Displacement-Time Graph for Constant Velocity">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        % Graph Paper
                        \draw[gray, thin, step=0.5] (0,0) grid (9,5);

                        % Axes
                        \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (9,0) node[below] {\text{Time (s)}};
                        \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (0,5.5) node[left] {\text{Displacement (m)}};

                        % Y-axis labels outside
                        \foreach \y in {10,20,30,40}
                            \draw (-0.2,\y/10) -- (0.2,\y/10) node[left=6pt] {\y};

                        % X-axis labels
                        \foreach \x in {2,4,6,8}
                            \draw (\x,-0.2) -- (\x,0.2) node[below=6pt] {\x};

                        % Graph Title
                        \node[above] at (4.5,5.5) { \text{Displacement-Time Graph for Constant Velocity}};

                        % Straight Line (Constant Velocity)
                        \draw[thick,blue] (0,0) -- (8,4);

                        % Mark Displacement at t=6s
                        \draw[dashed] (6,3) -- (6,-0.55) node[below] {$6s$};
                        \draw[dashed] (6,3) -- (-0.5,3) node[left] {$30m$};
                        
                        % Point at (6s, 30m)
                        \fill (6,3) circle (3pt);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                
            </image>
        </solution>

    </example>
    <example xml:id="auto_madbvf97">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_9rt6ksae">
                A car starts from rest and accelerates uniformly at <m>2 \,\text{m/s²}</m>  for <m>5</m> seconds. 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_r9o7wfz2">
                Draw the displacement-time graph.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_k3z5ivh3">
                Since acceleration is constant, the displacement follows the equation
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_zlqbqdii">
                <md>
                    <mrow> s = \frac{1}{2}at^{2} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_tm5qwpi5">
                for different time values:
            </p>
            <tabular halign="left" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row>
                    <cell>Time (s)</cell>
                    <cell>Displacement (m)</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>0.5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>4.5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>12.5</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
            <p xml:id="auto_92wgpuv4">
                Here is the graph
            </p>
            <image width="60%">
                <latex-image label="Displacement Time Graph for Uniform Acceleration">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                         % Graph Paper
                        \draw[gray, thin, step=0.5] (0,0) grid (7,7);

                        % Axes
                        \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (6.5,0) node[below] {\text{Time (s)}};
                        \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (0,7.0) node[left] {\text{Displacement (m)}};

                        % Y-axis labels outside
                        \foreach \y in {2,4,6,8,10,12,13}
                            \draw (-0.2,\y/2) -- (0.2,\y/2) node[left=6pt] {\y};

                        % X-axis labels
                        \foreach \x in {1,2,3,4,5}
                            \draw (\x,-0.2) -- (\x,0.2) node[below=6pt] {\x};

                        % Graph Title
                        \node[above] at (3,7.5) {\text{Displacement-Time Graph for Uniform Acceleration}};

                        % Parabolic Curve
                        \draw[thick,red] plot[smooth] coordinates {(0,0) (1,0.25) (2,1) (3,2.25) (4,4) (5,6.25)};

                        % Mark Displacement at t=5s
                        \draw[dashed] (5,6.25) -- (5,-0.5) node[below] {$5s$};
                        \draw[dashed] (5,6.25) -- (-0.5,6.25) node[left] {$12.5m$};
                        
                        % Point at (5s, 12.5m)
                        \fill (5,6.25) circle (3pt);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                
            </image>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example xml:id="auto_ttcfazmg">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_ka0wv0gp">
                A car moves in three different phases as shown below;
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_gy2kr6yo">
                The car starts from rest and accelerates uniformly.
                The car moves at a constant velocity.
                The car comes to a stop and remains at a fixed position.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_dwfividd">
                <ol xml:id="auto_s6xi0377" marker="a).">
                    <li xml:id="auto_8l6lzdo6">
                        <p xml:id="auto_gd53o4b2">
                            Sketch a displacement-time graph for the motion.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_zfeaj2xi">
                        <p xml:id="auto_czqynegv">
                            Identify the type of motion in each phase.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_0f5zdlsf">
                        <p xml:id="auto_h5bv68r3">
                            Determine the displacement at <m> \text{t = 3s, t = 6s, and t = 9s }. </m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_8zi3fgmr">
                <m>\text{0s to 3s}</m> - The displacement follows a curved path because the car is accelerating.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_2bbqp6j3">
                <m>\text{3s to 6s}</m> - The displacement increases linearly since the velocity is constant.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_t5erf7s6">
                <m>\text{6s to 9s}</m> - The displacement remains constant because the car has stopped.
            </p>
            <image width="60%">
                <latex-image label="Displacement-Time Graph for Three Phases of Motion">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                            % Graph Paper
                            \draw[gray, thin, step=0.5] (0,0) grid (10,8);

                            % Axes
                            \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (10.5,0) node[below] {\text{Time (s)}};
                            \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (0,8.5) node[left] {\text{Displacement (m)}};

                            % Y-axis labels outside
                            \foreach \y in {2,4,6,8,10,12,14,16}
                                \draw (-0.2,\y/2) -- (0.2,\y/2) node[left=7pt] {\y};

                            % X-axis labels
                            \foreach \x in {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9}
                                \draw (\x,-0.2) -- (\x,0.2) node[below=7pt] {\x};

                            % Graph Title
                            \node[above] at (5,8.8) {\text{Displacement-Time Graph for Three Phases of Motion}};

                            % Phase 1: Acceleration (\text{Curved Line})
                            \draw[thick,red] plot[smooth] coordinates {(0,0) (1,0.5) (2,2) (3,4.5)};
                            
                            % Phase 2: Constant Velocity (Straight Line)
                            \draw[thick,red] (3,4.5) -- (6,7);
                            
                            % Phase 3: Object at Rest (Horizontal Line)
                            \draw[thick,red] (6,7) -- (9,7);
                            
                            % Points
                            \fill (3,4.5) circle (2pt);
                            \fill (6,7) circle (2pt);
                            \fill (9,7) circle (2pt);
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                
            </image>
        </solution>
    </example>
