                                The runner then decelerates uniformly for <m>\text{ 5 seconds}</m> until stopping at <m>\text{ 100 meteres}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_9xijm1fs">
                    <ol xml:id="auto_u2atux2a">
                        <li xml:id="auto_6pqiwv7i">
                            <p xml:id="auto_dxtla9q9">
                                Sketch the displacement-time graph based on this motion.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_kj9h4qdm">
                            <p xml:id="auto_3wrz7a9a">
                                Determine the velocity during the constant speed phase.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_bo6nzb68">
                            <p xml:id="auto_rt2wt6m8">
                                Calculate the acceleration during the first <m>\text{ 5 seconds}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_1658r7my">
                            <p xml:id="auto_60x4b64j">
                                Find the total time taken to complete the journey.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_byxyvb1y">
                            <p xml:id="auto_cuykbs5e">
                                What is the average velocity for the entire motion?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <image width="60%">
                   <latex-image label="Displacement-Time Graph for Cyclist's Motion">
                            \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.9]
                                % Axes
                                \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (11,0) node[below] {Time (s)};
                                \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (0,6) node[left] {Displacement (m)};
                                
                                % Grid (optional)
                                \draw[gray, very thin] (0,0) grid (10,5);
                                
                                % Axis labels
                                % Time axis: 0,5,15,20
                                \foreach \x/\t in {0/0, 2.5/5, 7.5/15, 10/20}
                                    \draw (\x, -0.1) -- (\x, 0.1) node[below] {\t};
                                
                                % Displacement axis: 0,25,75,100
                                \foreach \y/\d in {0/0, 1.25/25, 3.75/75, 5/100}
                                    \draw (-0.1, \y) -- (0.1, \y) node[left] {\d};
                                
                                % Phase 1: Uniform acceleration (0-5s, 0-25m) - PARABOLA
                                % s = (1/2)*a*t², with s=25 at t=5 → a=2 m/s²
                                \draw[thick, blue] (0,0) parabola (2.5,1.25);
                                
                                % Phase 2: Constant velocity (5-15s, 25-75m) - STRAIGHT LINE
                                \draw[thick, blue] (2.5,1.25) -- (7.5,3.75);
                                
                                % Grid
                                \draw[gray, very thin, step=0.5] (0,0) grid (10,5);
                                
                                % Phase 3: Uniform deceleration (15-20s, 75-100m) - PARABOLA
                                % To get a parabola ending with zero slope at (10,5):
                                % Equation: s = 100 - 0.5*a*(20-t)², with a=2 m/s²
                                % But easier: draw parabola from (7.5,3.75) to (10,5) with bend
                                \draw[thick, blue] (7.5,3.75) parabola[bend at end] (10,5);
                                
                                % Mark points
                                \fill (2.5,1.25) circle (3pt) node[below right] {(5,25)};
                                \fill (7.5,3.75) circle (3pt) node[above left] {(15,75)};
                                \fill (10,5) circle (3pt) node[above right] {(20,100)};
                                
                                % Title
                                \node[above] at (5,5.5) {Displacement-Time Graph for Runner's Motion};
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                        </latex-image>
                </image>
                <p xml:id="auto_90qxxuva">
                    <ol xml:id="auto_p5t7jqm3">
                        <li xml:id="auto_l5oij6p2">
                            <p xml:id="auto_hjrwkfao">
                                The velocity during the constant speed phase is <m>\frac{50 \, \text{m}}{10 \, \text{s}} = 5 \, \text{m/s}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_js2etzli">
                            <p xml:id="auto_491jtm51">
                                The acceleration during the first <m>5</m> seconds is <m>\frac{25 \, \text{m}}{(5 \, \text{s})^2} = 2 \, \text{m/s}^2</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_j20d75n4">
                            <p xml:id="auto_mvsciol3">
                                The total time taken to complete the journey is <m>5 + 10 + 5 = 20 \, \text{seconds}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_kvb7p2u0">
                            <p xml:id="auto_n7ctevrj">
                                The average velocity for the entire motion is <m>\frac{100 \, \text{m}}{20 \, \text{s}} = 5 \, \text{m/s}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
        <exercise xml:id="auto_e6t45i4b">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_bal3b07z">
                    The displacement-time graph represents the motion of a cyclist
                    <ul xml:id="auto_0o1e1tur">
                        <li xml:id="auto_zy4g13bp">
                            <p xml:id="auto_jlzvmlf8">
                                From <m>\text{0 to 4 seconds}</m>, the cyclist moves forward at a uniform velocity.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_969iofx9">
                            <p xml:id="auto_dwq2jef3">
                                From <m>\text{4 to 8 seconds}</m>, the cyclist is stationary.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_acn3qob4">
                            <p xml:id="auto_e8hh38j0">
                                From  <m>\text{8 to 12 seconds}</m>, the cyclist moves back towards the starting point at a uniform velocity.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_pg0j5hvq">
                    <ol xml:id="auto_bdp41xcc">
                        <li xml:id="auto_lrqjxlmt">
                            <p xml:id="auto_mlkfysgf">
                                Sketch the graph for this motion.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_3n6igo88">
                            <p xml:id="auto_elrzwbdp">
                                What is the velocity during the first <m>\text{4 seconds}</m>?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_iy84wz35">
                            <p xml:id="auto_w9vru0yp">
                                What does the flat section of the graph indicate?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_wsjff303">
                            <p xml:id="auto_75la0nht">
                                Find the velocity during the last  <m>\text{4 seconds}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_jiiy39jk">
                            <p xml:id="auto_2so3iwp5">
                                Calculate the total displacement at the end of <m>\text{12 seconds}</m>.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                    <image>
                        <latex-image>
